        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 5:52PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 552 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Granville to near
McNabb. Movement was east at 30 mph. The cells may also produce a
few funnel clouds.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
North Utica, Tonica, Leonore, Oglesby, La Salle, Lostant, Peru, Cedar
Point, and Spring Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
